      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>Main work of <persName role="author" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14741GirgisY">Ǧirǧis al-Makīn ibn al-ʿAmīd (the Younger)</persName> containing an introduction on Christology, biblical exegesis,
               Coptic apologetics against Judaism, Islam, the Melkites and the Dyophysites as well as a refutation of astrology. It was translated into 
               Ethiopic by <persName role="translator" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8410Salikof">Salik</persName> towards 
               <date notBefore="1475" notAfter="1499">the end of the 15th century</date>. In the Ethiopic version it is attributed to a person 
               called "George, disciple of Anthony the Syrian". 
               According to the colophon of the work contained in some witnesses the text was translated from Greek into Arabic by <persName role="translator" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4374Gabreel">ገብርኤል፡ ወልደ፡ በትረክ፡</persName>.
               Different dates of the translation are mentioned: <date calendar="hijri" when-custom="315" when="0928">315 year of the Hijrah, that is 928 CE</date> 
               in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet110"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: BNFet110</span></ref> and <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient778"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: BLorient778</span></ref>; <date calendar="diocletian" when-custom="983" when="0991">983 year of martyrs, that is 991 CE</date> and 
               <date calendar="islamic" when-custom="665" when="1267">in the month <foreign xml:lang="ar">raǧab</foreign> in the year 665, that is 1267</date> in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd015"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: ESdd015</span></ref>. 
            </p>
         </abstract>
